reviews.review_text: Left the station... Note that the Passenger is missing from the first set. Saint of Circumstance wouldn't play for me, but maybe that was just an anomoly. The rest of the show plays. Great jams especially the first set.

Live At Terrapin Station Despite The Omissions (Passenger-1rst Set,Drums 2nd Set) This Is The Superior Sounding Copy Presently Available) A Grate Show In An Ole Time Venue Basketball Arena.The Home Of Lefty Driesell,Tom McMillan And (Rest In Peace) Len Bias. A 4 For The Omissions But Still The Best Of The Lot. Forever Grateful

my first show Just sayin.  It was my first show, and a little complicated for a newbie, at least until near the end when they broke out Truckin, R+R, and JohnnyB.  Complicated show, and I wish there was a good recording, but how can you do that at Cole Field House.  It's a field house for crying out loud.  Thank you to my big sister Cindy for taking me to my first show.
